<!-- Game Rounds -->
<h3>Game Rounds</h3>

<h4>1. Assignment</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Rebel assigns all missions first, then Imperial</li>
    <li>each player: assign any number of leaders to missions, 1 or 2 per mission placed on top of the face down mission card</li>
</ul>

<h4>2. Command</h4>

Rebel first, alternate between players

<p><b><u>Activate a System</u></b></p>
<ul>
    <li>place a leader from leader pool into <i>any</i> system</li>
    <li>note: if a leader does not have any tactic values, it cannot activate a system</li>
    <li>can move any ships from <b>adjacent</b> systems into the activated system</li>
    <li>cannot move units <i>out of</i> a system that already contains one of their leaders note: there is no specification as to <i>how</i> the leader got there, whether it was from an activation, a mission defense, etc.</li>
    <li>resolve combat if the system contains any opposing units</li>
    <li>after <i>Imperial ground troops</i> move into a system, the rebel player declares whether the base is there
        reveal the base before resolving a combat</li>
</ul>

<p><b><u>Reveal a mission</u></b></p>
<ul>
    <li>choose a face down mission with leader(s) assigned</li>
    <li>declare system for any mission attempt, but no further decisions yet</li>
    <li>place leader(s) in the declared system</li>
    <li>for mission "attempts", opponent can send 1 leader from leader pool to oppose
        if both players have a leader in the system, the mission is opposed and players roll to determine success/fail
        roll dice equal to combined skill icons on all leaders in the system
        ties favor defender
        [target] and [hit]: 1 success
        [lightsaber]: 2 successes</li>
    <li>note: for missions attempted/resolved in "rebel base" space, put leader in special rebel base space, not in the actual system on the board</li>
    <li>resolve: ability automatically occurs, cannot be opposed</li>
    <li>attempt: ability is only performed if the mission succeeds
        unopposed attempts automatically succeed</li>
    <li>missions attempted "against a leader" are attempted in that leader's system</li>
    <li>leader icon: any leader is eligible, but indicated leader adds +2 to success count</li>
</ul>

<p><b><u>Pass</u></b></p>
<ul>
    <li>turn is skipped for remainder of command phase</li>
    <li>proceed to Refresh when both players have passed</li>
</ul>

<h4>3. Refresh</h4>
<ol>
    <li>retrieve leaders</li>
    <li>draw 2 mission cards, discard down to 10 (projects count as missions, but objectives do not), cannot discard starting missions</li>
    <li>launch probe droids: Imperial secretly draws 2 cards from probe deck</li>
    <li>Rebel draws 1 objective</li>
    <li>advance time marker
        <ul>
            <li>recruit: each draws 2 action cards and chooses 1 leader shown on either card, then discard without effect (first game)
            may continue drawing action cards if neither have a recruitable leader
            later games: also keep the action card, place other at bottom of deck</li>
            <li>build: build 1 unit matching each resource icon in loyal/subjugated systems
            subjugated: only use left-most icon</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>deploy
        <ul>
            <li>start with rebel
        slide all units 1 space, deploy any that are ready
        deploy max 2 units in each system
        systems with an opponent's unit or a sabotage marker can neither build units in step 5, not deploy in step 6</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

