<h3>Definitions</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Capital Ship: ship with red health value; Death Star is a space station (not a capital ship)</li>
    <li>Figher: ship with black health value</li>
    <li>Gain unit: skip queue and place directly in system</li>
    <li>Ground unit: unit with orange resource icon</li>
    <li>Imperial System: system with an imperial loyalty marker or subjugation marker</li>
    <li>Neutral System: system without Rebel loyalty, Imperial loyalty, or subjugation (i.e. no markers at all)</li>
    <li>Populous System: resource icon(s) and a loyalty space</li>
    <li>Rebel System: system with a rebel loyalty marker and no subjugation marker</li>
    <li>Region: group of 4 systems, separated by thick orange borders</li>
    <li>Remote System: no loyalty or resource icons; always neutral, not deployment</li>
    <li>Ship: all units with blue resource icons, also Super Star Destroyers, Death Star (Under Construction)</li>
    <li>System: planet artwork, "outer space" area around planet, the name, resource icons (populous), and loyalty space (populous)</li>
    <li>Theater: ground vs space</li>
    <li>"win battle": opponent has 0 units from same theater
    no winner if all units destroyed
    cannot win the theater if opponent had no units at start</li>
</ul>

<h3>Captured Leaders</h3>
<ul>
    <li>do not oppose missions
        unless it is attempted "against a captured leader"</li>
    <li>do not prevent Rebel movement</li>
    <li>cannot be moved when retreating</li>
    <li>rescued if a second leader is captured</li>
    <li>do not reteurn to leader pool</li>
    <li>cannot be moved by Rebel</li>
    <li>do not prevent Rebel units from moving out of the system</li>
    <li>can be moved by Imperial like ground units, but does NOT count toward transport capacity</li>
    <li>captured leader will oppose missions used against it</li>
    <li>capturing a 2nd leader -> 1st captured leader is rescued</li>
    <li>no Imperial units in captured leader's system -> leader is rescued</li>
    <li>rescued: remove capture ring and place leader in "Rebel Base" space</li>
</ul>

<h3>Rescue</h3>
<ul>
    <li>place in "Rebel Base" space (unless revealed, then place in the system)</li>
    <li>auto-rescue if no Imperial units in captured leader's system</li>
    <li>after rescuing, any leaders assigned to the rescue may also move to the "Rebel Base" space, but only if involved in the rescue</li>
</ul>


<h3>Retreat</h3>
<ul>
    <li>cannot retreat to "Rebel Base"</li>
    <li>Imperial cannot retreat from a system with Death Star (Under Construction)</li>
    <li>must retreat *all* ships, but can leave ground units and tie fighters</li>
    <li>any leader can retreat, even those without tactic values</li>

    <li>move leader and all units from that system to an adjacent system</li>
    <li>cannot retreat if does not have a leader</li>
    <li>cannot retreat from the death star</li>
    <li>cannot retreat to a system that opponent moved units from to initiate the combat (no retreat-attacking)</li>
    <li>may only retreat to a system containing your units or has your loyalty marker</li>
</ul>

<h3>Deploy</h3>
<ul>
    <li>deploy max 2 units per system that is loyal or subjugated
    if cannot (or does not want to) deploy, leave on space 1
    cannot deploy to remote systems (because no loyalty)
    </li>
    <li>cannot deploy to a system with a sabotage marker, or any opponent ships or ground units</li>
    <li>Rebel can deploy to both the "Base" and the actual system (if loyal) while base is hidden
    while revealed, cannot deploy to "Base"
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Sabotage</h3>
<ul>
    <li>prevents system from using resource icons for building</li>
    <li>prevents deployment</li>
    <li>max 1 per system</li>
    <li>blocks abilities that "build" or "deploy" but other abilities that refer to resource icons are still valid</li>
    <li>stay on board until removed by a mission</li>
    <li>affect both factions</li>
</ul>

<h3>Subjugation</h3>
<ul>
    <li>any imperial ground units on a system without Imperial loyalty causes it to become subjugated</li>
    <li>remove token when no imperial ground units remain</li>
    <li>does not change the system's loyalty, only whether it is an imperial/neutral/rebel system</li>
    <li>players can gain/lose loyalty in a subjugated system</li>
</ul>

<h3>Win</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Imperial: imperial units in Rebel base's system and no Rebel units in the system
        <br />base must be revealed</li>
    <li>Rebel: reputation marker in same space as time marker</li>
</ul>

<h3>Rebel Base</h3>
<ul>
    <li>while hidden, Rebel can move between "base" and systems adjacent or containg base</li>
    <li>if Imperial ever has loyalty or ground units in the same system as the rebel base, it is immediately revealed</li>
    <li>while revealed, resource icons on "rebel base" space can be used, but units cannot be deployed in or moved to "rebel base" space, instead place in actual system</li>
    <li>missions can only be attempted at "Rebel Base" if specified by card</li>
</ul>

<h4>new base</h4>
<ul>
    <li>*may* choose a new base when using Rapid Mobilization, but it cannot be a system with Imperial loyalty or Imperial units</li>
    <li>reveal old base location, all units in "Rebel Base" go to the system, shuffle unchosen probe cards back into probe deck</li>
</ul>

<h4>Reveal</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Reveal when Imperial has loyalty or *ground units* in the base's system</li>
    <li>ships alone will not reveal the base</li>
    <li>when revealed, place all units in "Rebel Base" in the actual system</li>
    <li>finish all movement before revealing the base. Then resolve combat</li>
</ul>

<h4>While Revealed</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Rebel cannot deploy or move to "Rebel Base" space</li>
    <li>resource icons can still be used, unless there is an imperial unit in system or imperial loyalty</li>
    <li>any cards that refer to "Rebel Base" instead refer to the actual system</li>
</ul>

<h4>New Base</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Rapid Mobilization mission - resolve (and make all decisions) at end of command phase, immediately before refresh</li>
    <li>draw 4 (8), pick 1 (picking 1 is optional)</li>
    <li>reveal previous probe card, give to Imperial</li>
    <li>move all units and leaders from "Rebel Base" to previous base's system</li>
    <li>shuffle unchosen 3 (7) cards, put on bottom of probe deck</li>
    <li>cannot establish base in system with Imperial loyalty, Imperial units, or a destroyed system marker</li>
</ul>

<h3>Structures</h3>
<ul>
    <li>structures are destroyed if they are the Rebel's only remaining ground units AND there are imperial ground units</li>
    <li>if Rebel rolled at least 1 die in ground battle, structures are not auto-destroyed</li>
    <li>abilities that move units (yours or opponent's) do not apply to structures</li>
</ul>

<h3>Minor skills</h3>
<ul>
    <li>roll green die for the small icon</li>
    <li>small icon still counts toward skill requirements the same as a regular icon</li>
</ul>

<h3>Leader limit</h3>
<ul>
    <li>8 leader limit</li>
    <li>hard cap: remove a leader from the game if the limit is ever exceeded</li>
</ul>

<h3>Target Markers</h3>
<ul>
    <li>used by missions and objectives</li>
    <li>remove when player has a ground unit in the system and opponent does not</li>
    <li>destroying a system also removes any target markers (removal effect still resolves)</li>
</ul>

<h3>exp units</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Shield Bunker
        <ul>
            <li>Death Star (Under Construction) cannot be destroyed or dealt/assigned damage; immunity to Death Star Plans</li>
            <li>may be deployed to any system that contains an imperial ground unit and no Rebel units, regardless of loyalty</li>
            <li>while in a remote system without any Rebel units, Imperial may deploy there as if it were a loyal system; cannot be done same build step the bunker was deployed on</li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>Interdictor
        <ul>
            <li>prevents Rebel units from retreating, also prevents any special Rebel abilities that cause a retreat</li>
            <li>retreating is allowed if all interdictors are destroyed</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

